EKzMHI1tip8rC1-ZAy64yg
The ambiance and the food were excellent as always. Beautiful outdoor patio and beautiful weather. We had the buffalo mozzarella and Ahi Tuna Tartare as starters, which were both extremely fresh and delicious. The waiter was great and very knowledgeable. The food took longer than expected but not terrible... We had the beef tenderloin, short rib chile and cornish game hen. All excellent.   The only slightly negative experience was in the bar area before our reservation was ready. We ordered a round of drinks while we waited and the bartender/server seemed very impatient and short with us... Let's say, the opposite of engaging... Not a big deal but the ladies ordered Prosecco, which they did not have. Instead of telling us they don't serve Prosecco, they passed off a different cheap sparkling white wine hoping we wouldn't notice. Our server later confirmed that they do not serve Prosecco. Kinda shady.

